<h2 class="bold font-l">Bad-Anon</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
Wreck-It Ralph attends a support group for gaming villains, in lieu of his feelings of jealousy towards Fix-It Felix Jr. for being heralded as a hero. </p>
<p class='example_row'>Example of:<br><a href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TropaholicsAnonymous" class='trope-example-link'>Tropaholics Anonymous</a></p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="v1nz8k" data-video-descrip="&amp;quot;It's not her fault. She's programmed with the most tragic backstory ever.&amp;quot; Kohutt explains the reason behind Calhorn's personality, her fiance was killed during her wedding day because she didn't run a perimeter check." data-video-title="Calhorns Backstory" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/v1nz8k_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/cybug_wedding.png" data-video-trope="Main/WidowedAtTheWedding" data-video-tropename="Widowed at the Wedding" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="WesternAnimation/WreckItRalph" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/cybug_wedding.png">
